Where is our damage improvement?<br>
Are these supposed to make us feel better?<br>
<br>
There. it's out of my system. and on the &quot;rant&quot; board too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rendrac>Rendrac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/4/01 3:30:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rant: are you kidding?</span><hr size=1> I'm gonna be totally skeptical here.. but what if Verant is trying to get all the easiest stuff out of the way first?<br>
<br>
Nahh.. that'd be too un-Verant-like.<br>
<br>
<br>
-- Rendrac <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaineniyer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ainen Iyer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/5/01 5:52:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rant: are you kidding?</span><hr size=1> &quot;We are moving towards making wizards the masters of arcane transportation - Alan&quot;<br>
<br>
I just like to say that I did not fucking waste my time on playing a wizard to play a taxi bitch to others.  Arcane transportation??  Now I can sit my ass down and translocate lazy ass MOFOs to other zones all day long and make money? <br>
<br>
*dumb rage*<br>
<br>
Ainen<br>
57 Evoker <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/5/01 7:16:44 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rant: are you kidding?</span><hr size=1> He actually said TWO specialties, teleport being the focus of that particular response because it was by a Druid asking about translocates.  I'm the last person to defend Verant, especially about Wizards, but I think people need to actually read what was said more carefully.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile, I note Verant STILL thinks the game starts at level 35, and refuses to do anything with lower level characters. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ianaden>Ianaden </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/5/01 8:18:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> You have got to be kidding Verant</span><hr size=1> To quote directly from Absor's post<br>
<br>
Regardless of past perceptions or texts or class descriptions, Wizards are becoming masters of teleportation. They will probably never get foot speed enhancement spells, that sort of travel will always be the real of the Druid, Bard and Shaman.<br>
 <br>
Wizards right now have two specialties, damage and teleportation. They should be the masters of arcane magic and ripping holes in the fabric of space. Making them the masters of teleportation not only makes a lot of sense, it also adds a dimension to the class. <br>
<br>
Yes, we are moving toward making Wizards the master of arcane transportation. This seems like the right direction to take the class.<br>
<br>
Great, Verant has decided that our damage dealing is a specialty, not a class defining attribute. So they discard what they said we were and declare us the Masters of Arcane Transporation? WTF? I have struggled and tried to keep the faith for 2 years to be told that I am not what I thought I was, but a Taxi!<br>
<br>
Is this supposed to help us find groups? It isn't going to! I can see it now, I finally get a group and the entire time I get spammed with tells asking for a translocate! And the response &quot;I am in a group and cannot TP you&quot; will no longer shut them up. It will be, Cmon, you can translocate me! you dont have to go with me any more! Please! Cmon!<br>
<br>
It's always nice to know that Verant didn't listen to us on what we feel would balance the class but listened to all the whining that the other classes have done about hwo dificult it is for them to get from one zone to another!<br>
<br>
Well, I have had it! I give up!<br>
<br>
Ianaden, 50 wizard Xegony<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usilvius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/6/01 6:59:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rant: are you kidding?</span><hr size=1> If these ports go in at a lower level then 44 and are sold in solusek ro I'd be dancing for joy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uberylshadowhawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beryl Shadowhawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/01 1:18:15 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.unlv.edu/faculty/engstrom/images/bcard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rant: are you kidding?</span><hr size=1> I've never had a problem with self-ports, it's all those purple ones that cause me grief.  I am getting really tired of re-arranging my spellbook, tho.  With SoV self-ports and the new trans spells I'll need to move everything off two pages again.  Ports for 60 level wizzies should be skill based, like tracking.  Hit a button, a menu with all your ports pops up and you pick what you want to happen.  Now that would be nice.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufloydyancey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FloydYancey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/01 2:24:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rant: are you kidding?</span><hr size=1> Okay.. My question is.. To whom can we complain?  Seems that the EQ boards have been silenced.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/01 7:15:40 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yes...</span><hr size=1> I agree that the statement had two abilities listed.  However, Verant time and time again has suggested that our damage output or efficiency wouldn't need work NOR would they be supplimented, enhanced, or otherwise adjusted.  I think THAT is why I am more angry about this comment.  2 abilities, yet they stop to enhance THIS one without question.  Ok, I will leave open that MAYBE they are working on this one first and others might be to come.  I personally think they honestly believe that the Bane line allows them to wash their hands of the damage problems.<br>
<br>
And yes, I do believe this will do nothing but increase how many people bother us in game.  And it also gives us less of a reason to say NO.<br>
<br>
&quot;Can you port me?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;No.  I'm sorry.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Why?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm simply not porting at the moment.  In the middle of something.&quot;<br>
<br>
Under normal circumstances, that would be the end of it.  NOW the people will continue to pester us and say... <br>
<br>
&quot;Well don't you have translocate: Fay?  You won't have to move.  C'mon.&quot;<br>
<br>
After this, if we say &quot;No&quot; we are officially branded as the bad guy.<br>
<br>
It was more of a time and mana investment to port people than it is to heal, clarity, or most other abilites.  All I can say is, my ignore list is going to be maxed out VERY soon after these spells are implimented.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvortextwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VortexTwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/01 8:19:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yes...</span><hr size=1> donations will get a lot thinner. when's the last time you donated for a sow or clarity?<br>
<br>
I haven't in a LONG time... I'll bet that the translocates will see a drastic decline in people charging for ports.<br>
<br>
I'm all for that personally, but I know a lot of druids/wizards make quick and easy cash porting people around.<br>
<br>
I just know that in dozens of translocates now I've only seen donations 3 times. I ported people the other day because a full group of people were asking for ports I did so free of charge ... and upon porting the group the last two donated a sum total of 300pp. I'm betting that won't happen with the advent of translocates.<br>
<br>
I'm still debating if I'll even buy them. <p><p align="center"><img src="http://www.bigjaco.com/SG/eq_screenies/vort_sig52.jpg"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elrond>elrond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/01 11:42:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yes...</span><hr size=1> whats the big deal about these new translocates? i have had these spells for a long time now ( except they only seem to work for myself. heck, i think they mislabeled them and called them gates too!) So thru us, verant wants to offer gates to all classes huh? can anyone say Anon? Now all the melees are going to think its sooo easy for us to port them, we will never be left alone. and also there is no point in playing a wizard anymore since all the classes can gate everywhere too (at our expense).  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uteaenea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teaenea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/10/01 9:41:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yes...</span><hr size=1> I guess they figured, since wizards aren't grouping.  may as well use them for SOMETHING!<br>
